---
// Methodology modal: 3-column grid with full methodology content
---
<div class="modal-overlay" id="methodologyModal" role="dialog" aria-modal="true" aria-labelledby="methodologyTitle">
    <div class="modal-content">
        <div class="modal-header">
            <h2 id="methodologyTitle">Methodology</h2>
            <button class="modal-close" onclick="closeMethodology()" aria-label="Close methodology modal">
                <svg fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                    <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M6 18L18 6M6 6l12 12"></path>
                </svg>
            </button>
        </div>
        <div class="modal-body">
            <div class="modal-grid">
                <!-- How It Works -->
                <div class="modal-section">
                    <h3>How It Works</h3>
                    <div class="step-item">
                        <div class="step-num">1</div>
                        <div class="step-content">
                            <h4>Data Collection</h4>
                            <p>Reads Claude Code JSONL logs and Codex history.jsonl from your local machine. Nothing leaves your computer.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="step-item">
                        <div class="step-num">2</div>
                        <div class="step-content">
                            <h4>Message Extraction</h4>
                            <p>Filters to human-authored prompts. Excludes system commands, tool outputs, and agent sessions.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="step-item">
                        <div class="step-num">3</div>
                        <div class="step-content">
                            <h4>Embedding &amp; Classification</h4>
                            <p>Each prompt is embedded with <span>bge-small-en-v1.5</span> (local, offline). Cosine similarity to reference clusters scores 7 metrics in a single pass.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="step-item">
                        <div class="step-num">4</div>
                        <div class="step-content">
                            <h4>Persona Classification</h4>
                            <p>Four radar axes (Precision, Curiosity, Tenacity, Trust) are computed from embeddings. The dominant axis maps you to one of 5 personas.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <!-- All Metrics -->
                <div class="modal-section">
                    <h3>All Metrics</h3>
                    <div class="metric-group">
                        <h4>Volume</h4>
                        <p><span>Prompts</span> — your messages &middot; <span>Conversations</span> — chat sessions &middot; <span>Words</span> — total typed</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="metric-group">
                        <h4>Temporal</h4>
                        <p><span>Peak Hour/Day</span> — most active &middot; <span>Night Owl</span> — 11pm-4am % &middot; <span>Activity</span> — prompts/week trend</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="metric-group">
                        <h4>Hero Scores (Embedding)</h4>
                        <p><span>Human in the Loop</span> — how much you steer AI output. Higher = more hands-on review and iteration.<br/>
                        <span>Vibe Coder Index</span> — engineer vs vibe coder. Higher = more structured, spec-driven prompting.<br/>
                        <span>Politeness</span> — tone warmth. Higher = more courteous and collaborative.</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="metric-group">
                        <h4>Radar Axes (Embedding)</h4>
                        <p><span>Precision</span> — how detailed your instructions are<br/>
                        <span>Curiosity</span> — do you explore or execute?<br/>
                        <span>Tenacity</span> — how deep you go on one problem<br/>
                        <span>Trust</span> — how much you delegate to the AI</p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <!-- The 5 Personas -->
                <div class="modal-section">
                    <h3>The 5 Personas</h3>
                    <p style="font-size: 14px; color: var(--muted); margin-bottom: 20px; line-height: 1.6;">Derived from your 4 radar axes. The dominant dimension determines your persona:</p>
                    <div class="persona-list">
                        <div class="persona-cell highlight">
                            <strong>The Architect</strong>
                            High Precision, low Trust. Every prompt is a spec, every output gets reviewed.
                        </div>
                        <div class="persona-cell">
                            <strong>The Explorer</strong>
                            High Curiosity. You ask questions, dig into details, and follow threads wherever they lead.
                        </div>
                        <div class="persona-cell">
                            <strong>The Commander</strong>
                            High Precision, low Tenacity. Precise orders in short bursts — no wasted words.
                        </div>
                        <div class="persona-cell">
                            <strong>The Partner</strong>
                            High Tenacity. Long collaborative sessions, iterating until it's right.
                        </div>
                        <div class="persona-cell">
                            <strong>The Delegator</strong>
                            High Trust. You paint the vision and let AI handle the details.
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <p style="font-size: 13px; color: var(--muted); margin-top: 20px; border-top: 1px solid var(--border); padding-top: 16px;">All 7 metrics use embedding-based classification — no regex or keyword matching.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
